A **recurring deposit (RD) calculator** estimates the maturity value of fixed monthly deposits in a bank RD scheme. Indian bank RDs use quarterly compounding as the standard. Enter your monthly deposit amount, annual interest rate, and tenure in months — the calculator shows total deposited, interest earned, and final maturity value.

RDs are ideal for short-to-medium term goals (1–5 years) where capital safety is essential. Current RD rates in India range from 6.5% to 7.5% at major banks, with small finance banks offering up to 8.5%. RD interest is taxable at your applicable income slab rate.
